Quote: With respect to the leasing of the Auckland Islands by Dr Monckton, of Invercargill, the Evening Post says: ".. His scheme is mainly to use the island as a sheep and cattle run. He considers that its advantageous position with regard to the South Sea whalers and other shipping ought to ensure him an ample market for his surplus stock, and he purposes [sic] keeping up regular communication with the Bluff by means of a suitable schooner, which, we understand, he has already secured ..."
